
[1]downright

   DOWNRIGHT, adv.

   1. Right down; straight down; perpendicularly.

   A giant cleft downright.

   2. In plain terms; without ceremony or circumlocution.

   We shall chide downright.

   3. Completely; without stopping short; as, she fell downright into a
   fit.

                                DOWNRIGHT, a.

   1. Directly to the point; plain; open; artless; undisguised; as
   downright madness; downright nonsense; downright wisdom; downright
   falsehood; downright atheism.

   2. Plain; artless; unceremonious; blunt; as, he spoke in his downright
   way.
